      {
        "title": "tests/test_agent_normalize.py",
        "content": "from agent import _normalize_ats\n\ndef test_em_dash_and_smart_quotes_replaced_in_body_text():\n    html = \"<p>He said \\u201chello\\u201d \\u2014 twice</p>\"\n    out, counts = _normalize_ats(html)\n    assert \"\\u201c\" not in out and \"\\u2014\" not in out\n    assert counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1 and counts[\"smart-double-quote\"] == 2\n\ndef test_style_block_contents_untouched():\n    html = \"<style>.x::before{content:'\\u2014'}</style><p>\\u2014</p>\"\n    out, counts = _normalize_ats(html)\n    assert \"\\u2014\" in out.split(\"</style>\")[0]     # preserved inside <style>\n    assert counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1                     # only counts the <p> occurrence\n\ndef test_script_block_contents_untouched():\n    html = '<script>var x=\"\\u2014\";</script><p>\\u2014</p>'\n    out, counts = _normalize_ats(html)\n    assert out.startswith('<script>var x=\"\\u2014\"')\n\ndef test_tag_attributes_untouched():\n    html = '<a title=\"em\\u2014dash\">text\\u2014here</a>'\n    out, _ = _normalize_ats(html)\n    assert 'title=\"em\\u2014dash\"' in out    # attribute preserved\n    assert \"text-here\" in out               # body text normalized\n\ndef test_no_replacements_needed_returns_empty_counts():\n    out, counts = _normalize_ats(\"<p>plain ascii</p>\")\n    assert counts == {}\n```\n\n**7b. `cmd_db_new` — the most logic-dense function in the file; currently zero coverage on any branch.**\n- First-run (no marker) uses `since_days` window.\n- `--posted-days` filtering: dated-old dropped, undated kept by default, undated dropped with `--dated-only`.\n- Group-boundary truncation at `--limit` (never splits a `first_seen` group mid-way — the docstring explicitly calls this out as a correctness requirement for watermark safety).\n- `watermark` in output equals the `since` value when zero rows match.\n\n```python\n",
